# Paperclip — AI Company Orchestration Platform

Paperclip is an open-source Node.js + React platform that orchestrates teams of AI agents as a company. It is **not** an agent framework — it is the control plane that organises agents into org charts with goals, budgets, governance, and ticketing.

Repo: https://github.com/paperclipai/paperclip

## Repo Structure (pnpm monorepo)

```
server/          Express REST API + orchestration services
ui/              React + Vite board UI
packages/db/     Drizzle ORM schema, migrations, DB client
packages/shared/ Shared types, constants, validators, API path constants
packages/adapters/*  Agent adapter packages (OpenClaw, Claude Code, etc.)
cli/             CLI tool (`pnpm paperclipai …`)
doc/             Specs, product docs, developing guide
skills/          Runtime skill documents injected into agents
```

Workspace packages are declared in `pnpm-workspace.yaml`:
`packages/*`, `packages/adapters/*`, `server`, `ui`, `cli`.

## Requirements

- Node.js 20+
- pnpm 9.15+

## Setup & Running

### Quickstart (auto-onboard)
```sh
npx paperclipai onboard --yes
```

### Manual clone
```sh
git clone https://github.com/paperclipai/paperclip.git
cd paperclip
pnpm install
pnpm dev
```

- API server: `http://localhost:3100`
- UI: served on the same origin via dev middleware

Leave `DATABASE_URL` unset for local dev — an embedded PGlite database is auto-created at `~/.paperclip/instances/default/db`.

### Pre-flight: kill orphaned postgres

Before starting Paperclip, always kill any orphaned embedded postgres processes. Stale postgres locks will prevent the server from starting.

```powershell
Get-Process -Name "postgres" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force
```

Run this **every time** before `pnpm dev` or `pnpm dev:once`.

### Key commands
```sh
pnpm dev              # API + UI, watch mode
pnpm dev:once         # same but no file watching
pnpm dev:server       # server only
pnpm build            # build all packages
pnpm typecheck        # typecheck all packages
pnpm test:run         # run vitest tests
pnpm db:generate      # generate Drizzle migration after schema change
pnpm db:migrate       # apply pending migrations
pnpm paperclipai run  # auto-onboard + doctor + start (one-command)
```

### Health check
```sh
curl http://localhost:3100/api/health    # → {"status":"ok"}
curl http://localhost:3100/api/companies # → JSON array
```

### Reset local DB
```sh
rm -rf ~/.paperclip/instances/default/db
pnpm dev
```

## Architecture Overview

**Two layers:**

1. **Control Plane (this repo)** — agent registry, org chart, task/ticket system, budgets, goal hierarchy, heartbeat monitoring, governance gates.
2. **Execution Services (adapters)** — agents run externally (OpenClaw, Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Bash, HTTP) and report back via heartbeats.

The control plane does not run agents; it orchestrates them.

## Core Engineering Rules

1. **Company-scoped everything** — every domain entity belongs to a company; enforce company boundaries in routes and services.
2. **Keep contracts synchronised** — schema changes must cascade through `packages/db` → `packages/shared` → `server` → `ui`.
3. **Preserve control-plane invariants:** single-assignee tasks, atomic issue checkout, approval gates, budget hard-stop, activity logging.
4. **Database changes:** edit `packages/db/src/schema/*.ts`, export from `schema/index.ts`, run `pnpm db:generate`, then `pnpm -r typecheck`.
5. **Verification before done:** `pnpm -r typecheck && pnpm test:run && pnpm build`.

## API Conventions

- Base path: `/api`
- Board access = full-control operator context
- Agent access = bearer API key (hashed at rest), company-scoped
- All mutations must write activity log entries
- HTTP error codes: `400 / 401 / 403 / 404 / 409 / 422 / 500`

## Data & Secrets

- Local storage: `~/.paperclip/instances/default/data/storage`
- Secrets use local encryption by default; master key at `~/.paperclip/instances/default/secrets/master.key`
- Override via `PAPERCLIP_SECRETS_MASTER_KEY` or `PAPERCLIP_SECRETS_MASTER_KEY_FILE`
- Strict mode (`PAPERCLIP_SECRETS_STRICT_MODE=true`) requires secret refs for `*_API_KEY`, `*_TOKEN`, `*_SECRET`

## Docker Alternative

```sh
docker compose -f docker-compose.quickstart.yml up --build
```

## Key Concepts

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Company | Top-level tenant; full data isolation per company |
| Org Chart | Agent hierarchy with roles, reporting lines, titles |
| Goal | Cascading objectives: company → team → agent → task |
| Heartbeat | Scheduled wake-up; agents check in, get work, act |
| Ticket/Issue | Tracked unit of work with conversation threading |
| Budget | Monthly token spend cap per agent; auto-pause on limit |
| Governance | Board approval gates for hires, strategy, config changes |
| Skill | Runtime-injected context document for agent capabilities |
